==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: magnetic north
<hw>magnetic north</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The direction in which the
north-pointing end of a compass needle points; at low latitudes it is
close to geographic (true) north, but deviates substantially from true
north as one nears the north pole.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> north, compass north.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magneticness</ent>⟦br⟧
